folder: Central Park West & 77th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
North On Central Park West from 81st Street. At the left is seen the Beresford.
About 1925.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 77th Street

folder: Central Park West & 77th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park West, west side, at 81st Street, showing the 81st Street side of the old Hotel Beresford, which will be demolished the following summer. The park in the foreground is the northeastern corner of Manhattan Square, which is on the west side of Central Park West from 77th to 81st Streets.

July 13, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 77th Street

folder: Central Park West & 77th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park West, from 77th to 79th Streets, showing the New York Historical Society on the S.W. corner of 77th Street and the American Museum of Natural History in Manhattan Square. The cornerstone of the oldest wing, shown here, was laid in 1874. Part of the Central Park bridle path and Lake are shown in the foreground.

February 2, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
